1 (h) A motion by any Senator to change that Senator's vote must be made in open
2 session on the same legislative day as the vote is taken. This subsection may not be suspended.
3 RULE 30. (Reserved for future use).
4 V. COMMITTEES
5 RULE 31. Appointment of committees. – The President Pro Tempore of the Senate
6 shall have the exclusive right and authority to appoint the membership of all committees,
7 including regular and select, and to appoint committee chairs and vice-chairs and to establish
8 select committees, but this does not exclude the right of the Senate by resolution to establish
9 select committees. Upon the recommendation of the Committee on Rules and Operations of the
10 Senate, the Senate may alter the name, number, and composition of the standing committees by
11 a three-fifths vote of the membership of the Senate present and voting.
12 RULE 32. List of standing/select committees. – The standing committees shall be:
13 Agriculture, Energy, and Environment
14 Appropriations/Base Budget
15 Appropriations on Department of Transportation
16 Appropriations on Education/Higher Education
17 Appropriations on General Government and Information Technology
18 Appropriations on Health and Human Services
19 Appropriations on Justice and Public Safety
20 Appropriations on Agriculture, Natural, and Economic Resources
21 Commerce and Insurance
22 Committee of the Whole Senate
23 Education/Higher Education
24 Elections
25 Finance
26 Health Care
27 Judiciary
28 Pensions and Retirement and Aging
29 Regulatory Reform
30 Rules and Operations of the Senate
31 State and Local Government
32 Transportation
33 RULE 33. Notice of committee meetings. – (a) Public notice of all committee
34 meetings shall be given in the Senate. The required notice may be waived as to any meeting by
35 the attendance at that meeting of all of the members of the committee or by personal waiver.
36 (b) The chair of the committee shall notify or cause to be notified the sponsor of
37 each bill that is set for hearing or consideration before the committee as to the date, time, and
38 place of that meeting.
39 (c) The published calendar shall reflect those committee notices received in the
40 Office of the Principal Clerk prior to 3:30 P.M. or as announced in the daily session.
41 RULE 34. Membership of committees; quorum. – (a) Membership on standing
42 committees shall consist of no fewer than five Senators, including the chairs and vice-chairs and
43 ranking minority members.
44 The President Pro Tempore shall have the exclusive right and authority to determine
45 the total number of members and the number of members of each political party of each
46 committee. No Senator shall hold membership on more than 12 standing committees unless the
47 Committee on Rules and Operations of the Senate provides otherwise.
48 A quorum of the Appropriations/Base Budget and Finance Committees shall consist
49 of a majority of the committee. A quorum of any other committee shall consist of either the chair
50 and five members or a majority of the committee, whichever is fewer.
Senate Resolution 1-First Edition Page 9

